The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Jan 1. (PTI): The parents of a 15-year-old girl donated her organs after she died following brain surgery at Jaslok hospital in south Mumbai on Wednesday.           
	The girl was admitted to the hospital on December 23 with a brain tumour and slipped into a coma after surgery the same day. When she was declared dead, her parents donated her kidneys and liver.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission has directed a surgeon to pay Rs 1 lakh as compensation for medical negligence. He was unable to diagnose the disease of a patient despite having enough clinical evidence the commission ruled. An illness in the left foot of the patient had aggravated and spread, leading to permanent disfigurement of the limb.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): India introduced tourist visa-on-arrival for five countries on Friday to help genuine tourists who plan their visits at short notice. This has been introduced for one year on an experimental basis. The countries are Finland, Japan, Luxembourg, New Zealand and Singapore.                   
	Srinagar (PTI): A couple from Uttar Pradesh were found dead in a hotel room in Gulmarg on Friday, police said. Prashant Swamy, 29, and his wife Joyti, 23, had come to celebrate the New Year in Gulmarg. The cause of death appears to be a leak in the gas heater that was being used to ward off cold.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): The Jammu Bar Association has decided to suspend work on January 2 in protest against the report by Justice Saghir Ahmed on Centre-state relations, which they dubbed Kashmir- centric. A protest rally would be organised on that day at City Chowk.                  
	 Shajapur (PTI): One person was killed and five injured following violence between two groups during a cricket match in Srinagar. Police have imposed an indefinite curfew on Friday evening.                                                                                                                                              
